class Solution {
    public boolean doesAliceWin(String s) {
        int vowelCount = 0;
        for (char c : s.toCharArray()) {
            if (isVowel(c)) {
                vowelCount++;
            }
        }
        return vowelCount > 0;
    }

    private boolean isVowel(char c) {
        return c == 'a' || c == 'e' || c == 'i' || c == 'o' || c == 'u';
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(N)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution iterates through the string once to count the vowels. Alice can win if there's at least one vowel. The isVowel helper function checks if a character is a vowel. The main strength is its linear time complexity and constant space complexity.
